tags.name: Mount Hillyer
tags.note: Named for Mary Hillyer (ca.1865-1933), described by author John W. Robinson as "a competent and much beloved clerk" who worked during the 1920's in the office of William V. Mendenhall, Angeles N.F. Supervisor (1929-57)
